text: Oroville is a city in California. It is the county seat of Butte County. The population was 20,042 at the 2020 census. Oroville is thought to be the gateway to Lake Oroville and Feather River recreational areas. == References == Category:1900s establishments in California Category:1906 establishments in the United States Category:Cities in California Category:County seats in California Category:Settlements in Butte County, California
